comments: Adebayo (MIA) brings his hands toward Jones' (SAS) back and marginal contact occurs as Adebayo releases away to roll after setting the pick.
Jones (SAS) brings his right hand toward Lowry's (MIA) path and marginal contact occurs as Lowry is passing at the end of the drive.
Vincent (MIA) and Landale (SAS) engage and disengage with one another as Landale sets the pick.
Vincent (MIA) brings his left forearm toward Landale's (SAS) front and marginal contact occurs as Landale mishandles the pass.
Adebayo (MIA) gathers the ball on his right foot and takes two steps before attempting the shot.

Bates-Diop (SAS) makes clean contact with the ball after Adebayo's (MIA) gather. Jones (SAS) brushes Adebayo's right arm as Adebayo uses his left hand to pin the ball against his side, and Adebayo is able to move through the marginal contact to continue on his path toward the rim.
Adebayo (MIA) falls to the floor after attempting the shot and incidental body contact occurs with Jones (SAS).
Landale (SAS) and Vincent (MIA) engage and disengage with one another in the lane.
Vincent (MIA) brings his left forearm toward Richardson's (SAS) path and marginal contact occurs to Richardson's front as he elevates to pass the ball.
Richardson (SAS) releases the pass prior to his left foot landing out of bounds.
Lowry (MIA) contests the jump shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Vassell's (SAS) upper body during the follow-through.
Landale (SAS) is turning his body as he jumps toward Lowry (MIA) and makes contact that affects his driving shot attempt.

Lowry (MIA) brings his off-arm toward Landale (SAS) during the driving shot attempt and marginal contact occurs with Landale's upper half, including some made to his head/neck area. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Herro (MIA) is already losing control of the ball as a result of the contact made with his teammate and incidental arm contact is made by Jones (SAS) thereafter during rebounding.
Jones (SAS) commits a take foul on Adebayo (MIA).
Lowry (MIA) jumps forward in pursuit of the rebound and marginal contact occurs with Bates-Diop's (SAS) left side as he secures the ball.
Herro (MIA) turns toward Bates-Diop (SAS) and marginal body contact occurs as Bates-Diop drives into the lane.
Adebayo (MIA) jumps vertically and absorbs the body contact that occurs with Bates-Diop (SAS) before cleanly deflecting the pass attempt.
Adebayo (MIA) brings his arm down and marginal contact occurs with Bates-Diop's (SAS) upper half as he is passing.
Herro (MIA) and Landale (SAS) engage and disengage with one another during rebounding.
Herro (MIA) rests his forearm on Landale's (SAS) front and marginal contact occurs as Landale attempts the put-back.
Jones (SAS) moves forward toward Lowry (MIA) and marginal contact occurs with Lowry's upper half as he is making the pass.
Jones (SAS) commits a take foul on Herro (MIA).
Prior to the timeout being awarded, Bates-Diop (SAS) and Herro (MIA) engage and disengage with one another during the inbound.
Prior to the timeout being awarded, Richardson (SAS) engages and disengages with Vincent (MIA) during the inbound.
Jones (SAS) initiates contact with Vincent's (MIA) arm and side as he receives the inbound pass.
Adebayo (MIA) grasps and then quickly releases Landale's (SAS) jersey during the inbound.
Adebayo (MIA) and Herro (MIA) legally contest Richardson's driving shot attempt.
Landale (SAS) elevates for the rebound and marginal body contact occurs with Adebayo (MIA) as Adebayo secures the ball.
